C makes it obvious were you use that dynamism and where you don't.  Syntactic sugar doesn't really make that much of a difference and also restricts more creative uses.The C syntax is not really that complicated.  Dynamic dispatch and virtual methods was already in the article.  Here is inheritance:    struct Subclass {
        struct Baseclass base;
